records.addlTxt:
Defendant Megan L Miller appeared by video.  Attorney Christin Marie Saint Pierre appeared by video for Megan L Miller.  Attorney Anthony A. Lambrecht appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
NO CONTEST plea to the charge in count 2, possess amphetamine.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST plea to the charge in count 5, resisting or obstructing.  Convicted.
State moves to dismiss count 1 outright.  Motion granted.
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 3, 4 and 6.  Motion granted.
Sentence withheld and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety except for any prescribed medications;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
5) Pay court costs;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Provide DNA sample
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
Defendant has credit for 14 days.
